# ORIG TITLE    New Year’s Eve robbery at Paris Apple store . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Thousands of euros worth of goods have been stolen from an Apple store in Paris. French police are refusing to confirm whether thieves got away with up to a million euros worth of items – including iPads, iPhones and Mac computers. The burglary at store located behind the Paris Opera happened three hours after closing time on New Year’s Eve. Police say the robbery was well-planned and at a time the majority of officers were busy monitoring New Year’s Eve celebrations on the Champs Elysees. 
